claim: Flublok contains 45 micrograms (mcg) of HA per strain vs 15 mcg of HA per strain in a standard-dose influenza vaccine.
explanation: A table of solicited adverse events (e.g., fever ≥100.4°F, fatigue, myalgia, headache, nausea, chills) with counts and percentages by study group, showing severity grades and incidence over the 7-day post-vaccination period. does not support the claim because the table only presents adverse event frequencies and contains no information on HA microgram content per strain in Flublok or standard-dose vaccine
